<HEAD>ADVERTISEMENT.</HEAD>
<P>TEACHERS who turn grace into la&s;civiou&s;ne&s;s, have men's per&s;ons in admiration becau&s;e of ad|vantage. Jude <HI>4, 16.</HI> With &s;uch, nothing can be too bad to &s;ay of any who expo&s;e their darling errors, while they will not allow us to be charitable, if we cannot think them all to be good men, whom they ad|mire. But in what fellows, I have endeavoured to open principles and facts plainly, and to leave every reader to judge of men by their fruits, and not by their plau&s;ible pretences.</P>
<CLOSER><DATELINE><HI>Middleborough,</HI><DATE><HI>July 25, 1789.</HI></DATE></DATELINE></CLOSER>
